{"id": 243299226, "title": "This life with Nthabi Nhlapo | The good, the bad and the ugly of a stronger rand", "text": "For those who earn in foreign currencies such as the dollar, an improved rand on the back of GNU talks meant earnings were worth less when exchanged for rands. Nthabi Nhlapo writes it moved the figurative saying, \"the high cost of democracy\" into the literal. Few things would make losing money due to the exchange rate something worth celebrating and South Africans living abroad got the slightest of that paradoxical kind of joy when the rand gained strength against major currencies. For those who earn in foreign currencies such as the dollar, and in my case the Korean won (KRW), this means suddenly their earnings were worth less when exchanged for rands. It moved the figurative saying, \"the high cost of democracy\" into the literal.", "summary": "For those who earn in foreign currencies such as the dollar, an improved rand on the back of GNU talks meant earnings were worth less when exchanged for rands. Nthabi Nhlapo writes it moved the figurative saying, \"the high cost of democracy\" into the literal.", "url": "https://www.news24.com/news24/opinions/columnists/nthabiseng-nhlapo/this-life-with-nthabi-nhlapo-the-good-the-bad-and-the-ugly-of-a-stronger-rand-20240629", "image": "https://cdn.24.co.za/files/Cms/General/d/11951/d6082aa4e73e41c2be4b91c230ebc684.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 04:06:30", "author": "Nthabi Nhlapo", "authors": ["Nthabi Nhlapo"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ZA", "sentiment": -0.348}